cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with security and privacy issues in peer-to-peer networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves algorithms and network structures, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper proposes a novel algorithm to address the problem of whitewashing, which could be considered as a solution to a social network problem (cs.SI). The use of temporary identities and reputation management also involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
